    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Aster albus are fever, due to its antipyretic properties which help to reduce body temperature. Aster albus contains flavonoids and saponins that have anti-inflammatory effects, making it effective in treating arthritis and other inflammatory conditions. The plant's antioxidant properties also help to protect against cell damage caused by oxidative stress, which can contribute to the development of neurodegenerative diseases such as Alzheimer's. Its antimicrobial properties make it useful in treating skin infections like eczema, while its diuretic properties help to alleviate symptoms of urinary tract infections. Additionally, Aster albus has been used to treat respiratory issues such as bronchitis due to its expectorant properties.",
