    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Aster albus are antioxidant and antimicrobial activities, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids. This plant exhibits anti-inflammatory properties, which are mediated by saponins and volatile oils that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. The antimicrobial activity of Aster albus is also responsible for its use in treating various infections, including those caused by bacteria and fungi. Additionally, Aster albus has been found to possess cardioprotective properties, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids that inhibit the oxidation of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol and reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease. The antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties of Aster albus also contribute to its use in treating respiratory tract infections and allergies.",
