    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Aster albus are flavonoids, phenolic acids, and essential oils. Flavonoids such as kaempferol, quercetin, and isorhapontigenin exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, protecting against oxidative stress and inflammation. Phenolic acids like ferulic acid and sinapic acid have antimicrobial and antifungal activities, contributing to the plant's potential in treating infections. Essential oils, primarily containing sesquiterpenes and diterpenes, display antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects, supporting wound healing and immune system modulation. These bioactive compounds contribute to the plant's therapeutic properties, warranting further research into its potential applications in traditional medicine.",
