    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Aster albus are infusion, tincture, tea, salve, and decoction. Infusion and tea are made by steeping the flowers in hot water to create a mild and soothing drink, often used to calm digestive issues. Tincture is prepared by steeping the flowers in a solvent like ethanol to create a concentrated liquid used to treat various health conditions. A salve is made by infusing the flowers in a carrier oil to create a topical cream for skin issues, while decoction involves boiling the roots in water to create a more potent and bitter liquid used for treating various ailments. These preparations are used due to Aster albus's properties as an anti-inflammatory and antioxidant.",
